            "pageContent": "Cost and Convenience\nGovernment grants available for eligible home charging points.\nTaxation benefits may be available compared to petrol and diesel cars, for example \nroad tax and Benefit in Kind(BIK). Find out more here\nReduced servicing requirements due to fewer moving parts .\nCheaper running costs vs diesel or petrol cars.\nEVs can be charged at home and can be charged overnight, offering more \nconvenience and less time spent at a petrol station.\nThere could be specific local incentives that you should look into via your local \ncouncil i.e. exemption from congestion charges, free parking etc.\nIcon\nDescription \nautomatically\ngenerated\nIcon\nDescription\nautomatically\ngenerated\nIcon\nDescription \nautomatically\ngenerated\nIcon\nDescription \nautomatically\ngenerated\nIcon\nDescription \nautomatically\ngenerated\nIcon\nDescription \nautomatically\ngenerated\nInternal\nIcon\nDescription \nautomatically \ngenerated\nElectric cars have a 50 to 80% better carbon footprint than petrol cars.\nClick the icons to \nfind out more.",
